  "findings": [
    "The previous single LL-HLS packager was a hard bottleneck; per-rendition packaging moved 16-channel p99 to about 6.8 ms and 32-channel p99 to about 28.3 ms locally.",
    "At 64 channels the laptop is not a reliable sizing proxy. The best PCM run completed without missing parts but had p99 around 690 ms; later runs varied under local CPU and sender contention.",
    "At 128 channels the local host cannot sustain the full PCM-source path at 5 ms parts; source sending itself stretched to 7.3-8.2 s for 5 s of media.",
    "FLAC-source tests removed server-side FLAC encoding work and reached zero HLS queue drops, but high latency remained because the local sender and server contend on the same host and the deterministic signal barely compresses at 5 ms frames.",
    "The next authoritative sizing run requires separated sender, contributor, and reader/load machines."
  ],
